-- Mitsui Chemicals to Set Up $330 Million Venture With Sinopec in Shanghai
-- B y   G o   O n o m i t s u
-- 2010-10-28T04:50:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/mitsui-chemicals-to-set-up-330-million-venture-with-sinopec-in-shanghai.html
China Petroleum and Chemical Corp.
and Mitsui Chemicals Inc. agreed to form a 50-50 rubber venture
and build a plant in Shanghai. The Japanese chemicals maker said
investment will amount to 27 billion yen ($331 million). The
venture is scheduled to be formed next year, Mitsui Chemicals
said in a release on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Go Onomitsu in Tokyo at 
 gonomitsu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
